Jesus, this whole song just screams messed up childhood. I can deeply identify with this, the lyrics and the imagery. It's so well made. This is truly art. I suffer from a bad case of not being able to read people's facial expressions and feeling estranged from the world as a whole and other people. I can read extreme emotions somewhat well, but then again they seem like distorted reality or cinema to me. Call it Aspergers or call it Childhhod Trauma. The scenes with the mannequins reflect so hard how i see everyday life (yes it is a little exaggerated though), just life forms that I cannot understand and seem strange to me, kind of menacing not knowing why they are here with me or whether they are friendly, but here and there, when a strong emotion flickers through, I can see their emotions very clearly, although always wondering whether they are truly genuine or not.  It's eerie how much this video reflects on a metaphorical level what I am dealing witth everyday. Don't know if it was intended this way, but Sub Urban is definitely a genius. Never had anything else trigger a feeling of familiarity inside of me like that before, not even (or especially not) other people.
